.IP "\fBXmNfontList\fP"
Specifies the font of the text used in the widget.  If this value is NULL
at initialization, it is initialized by looking up the parent hierarchy of
the widget for an ancestor that is a subclass of the XmBulletinBoard,
VendorShell, or XmMenuShell widget class.  If such an ancestor is found,
the font list is initialized to the appropriate default font list of the
ancestor widget (XmNdefaultFontList for VendorShell and XmMenuShell,
XmNlabelFontList or XmNbuttonFontList for XmBulletinBoard).  Refer to
\fBXmFontListCreate(3X)\fP for more information on the creation and
structure of a font list.
.IP "\fBXmNlabelInsensitivePixmap\fP"
Specifies a pixmap used as the button face if \fBXmNlabelType\fP is
\fBXmPIXMAP\fP and the button is insensitive.
.IP "\fBXmNlabelPixmap \fP"
Specifies the optional pixmap displayed.  \fBXmPIXMAP\fP.
.IP "\fBXmNlabelString\fP"
Specifies the compound string displayed.  Refer to \fBXmStringCreate(3X)\fP
or \fBXmStringCreateLtoR(3X)\fP for more information on the creation and
structure of compound strings.
.IP "\fBXmNmarginBottom\fP"
Specifies the amount of spacing that is to be left after the bottom margin
(\fBXmNmarginHeight\fP) of the widget, before the label is drawn.  
.IP "\fBXmNmarginHeight\fP"
Specifies the amount of blank space between the bottom edge of the top
shadow and the label, and the top edge of the bottom shadow and the label.
.IP "\fBXmNmarginLeft\fP"
Specifies the amount of spacing that is to be left after the left margin
(\fBXmNmarginWidth\fP) of the widget before the label is drawn.  This may
be modified by SgIconGadget's subclasses.  
.IP "\fBXmNmarginRight\fP"
Specifies the amount of spacing that is to be left after the right margin
(\fBXmNmarginWidth\fP) of the widget before the label is drawn.
.IP "\fBXmNmarginTop\fP"
Specifies the amount of spacing that is to be left after the top margin
(\fBXmNmarginHeight\fP) of the widget before the label is drawn.
.IP "\fBXmNmarginWidth\fP"
Specifies the amount of blank space between the right edge of the left
shadow and the label, and the left edge of the right shadow and the label.
.IP "\fBXmNspacing\fP"
Specifies the amount of blank space between the  label and the pixmap.
.IP "\fBXmNrecomputeSize\fP"
Specifies a Boolean value that indicates whether the widget attempts to be
big enough to contain the label.  If True, an \fBXtSetValues\fP with a new
label string or pixmap, margins, font, or label type causes the widget to
shrink or expand to exactly fit the new label string or pixmap.  If False,
the widget never attempts to change size on its own.
.IP "\fBXmNstringDirection\fP"
Specifies the direction in which the string is to be drawn.  The 
following are the values:
.rS
.IP \(bu 3
\fBXmSTRING_DIRECTION_L_TO_R\fP \(em left to right 
.IP \(bu 3
\fBXmSTRING_DIRECTION_R_TO_L\fP \(em right to left
.rE
.P
The value of this resource is determined at creation time.  If the widget's
parent is a manager, this value is inherited from the widget's parent,
otherwise it is set to XmSTRING_DIRECTION_L_TO_R.
.sp 1
