.SS "Callback Information"
The following structure is returned with each callback:
.sp 1
.nf
.ta .25i 1.50i
\fBtypedef struct\fP
{
	\fBint\fP	\fIreason\fP;
	\fBXEvent	\fI* event\fP;
} \fBXmAnyCallbackStruct\fP;
.fi
.fi
.sp 1
.IP "\fIreason\fP" .75i
Indicates why the callback was invoked.  For this callback, \fIreason\fP is
set to \fBXmCR_HELP\fP.
.IP "\fIevent\fP" .75i
Points to the \fBXEvent\fP that triggered the callback.
